Class SaveManager

java.lang.Object
cz.cvut.copakond.sweetfluffysheep.model.utils.json.SaveManager
public class SaveManager extends Object
SaveManager is responsible for managing the JSON data structure used for saving game levels. It provides methods to add various types of data to the JSON object, including level information, player information, tiles, enemies, and items.

  • Method Details

    • addDefaultLevelData

      public void addDefaultLevelData(boolean isDefaultLevel)
      Returns the JSON object containing the level data.
      Parameters:
      isDefaultLevel - Indicates whether the level is the default level or not.

    • addStartGoalData

      public void addStartGoalData(Start start, Goal goal)
      Adds start and goal data to the JSON object. The start and goal positions are rounded to the nearest integer.
      Parameters:
      start - The starting position of the player.
      goal - The destination point for the player.

    • addMapSizeData

      public void addMapSizeData(int[] mapSize)
      Adds map size data to the JSON object. The map size is represented as an array of integers.
      Parameters:
      mapSize - An array of integers representing the map size.

    • addLevelInfo

      public void addLevelInfo(Map<String,Integer> levelInfo)
      Adds level information to the JSON object. The level information includes time limit, number of sheep, goal sheep, max arrows, creation time, and updated time.
      Parameters:
      levelInfo - A map containing level information.

    • addPlayerInfo

      public void addPlayerInfo(Map<String,String> playerInfo)
      Adds player information to the JSON object. The player information includes the creator name and updated time.
      Parameters:
      playerInfo - A map containing player information.

    • addTilesData

      public void addTilesData(List<Tile> tiles)
      Adds tiles data to the JSON object. The tiles data includes the position and texture type of each tile.
      Parameters:
      tiles - A list of Tile objects representing the tiles in the level.

    • addEnemiesData

      public void addEnemiesData(List<Wolf> enemies)
      Adds enemies data to the JSON object. The enemies data includes the position and direction of each enemy.
      Parameters:
      enemies - A list of Wolf objects representing the enemies in the level.

    • addItemsData

      public void addItemsData(List<Item> items)
      Adds items data to the JSON object. The items data includes the position, effect type, and duration of each item.
      Parameters:
      items - A list of Item objects representing the items in the level.
